-- Flagstone First-Half Disasters Cost Up to $55 Million in Quarter
-- B y   A n d r e a   L u d t k e
-- 2012-02-08T21:40:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-08/flagstone-first-half-disasters-cost-up-to-55-million-in-quarter.html
Flagstone Reinsurance Holdings SA (FSR) ,
the Luxembourg-based reinsurer, said catastrophes that occurred
in the first half cost $50 million to $55 million in the fourth
quarter.  The reinsurer also had $13 million to $18 million in costs
from the floods in  Thailand , the company said in a statement
today distributed by  Business Wire .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrea Ludtke in New York at 
 aludtke@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Kraut at   dkraut2@bloomberg.net  